# {{PROJECT_NAME}} — Agent Contracts

> The canonical conventions for every agent in this repo's fleet. Orchestrators read
> this file first. Pair with `PATTERNS.md` (rules index) and the routing matrix in
> `.agentic/guides/agent-registry.md`.

**Canonical source.** Each agent's full contract lives in
`{{AGENTS_CANONICAL_DIR}}<name>.md` (frontmatter declares `write_scope`; body is the
instruction set). `.claude/agents/<name>.md` and `.claude/commands/<name>.md` are thin
pointers that bootstrap into the canonical contract — the contract body is never
duplicated, only referenced. Keep pointer layers in sync with the canonical directory.

**Routing.** Which asset owns which intent is defined once, in
[`.agentic/guides/agent-registry.md`](.agentic/guides/agent-registry.md) — this file
links to it and never restates it. To find "who handles X", consult the registry (or
ask the `dispatcher` agent, which outputs exactly one owning path).

## Fleet invariants

1. **Write scope is absolute.** An agent that writes outside the `write_scope` in its
   contract frontmatter is a bug; treat it as you would a security breach. Enforced at
   PreToolUse by `.claude/hooks/write_scope_guard.py` when an orchestrator has set the
   active-agent lock (`.agentic/state/active-agent.json`).
2. **Orchestrator-only spawning.** Peer agents never spawn each other; only
   orchestrating commands (and the human) spawn subagents. This keeps every spawn
   auditable and every write attributable.
3. **Gate agents are read-only** and must emit a literal `PASS` token for the
   pipeline to advance. No PASS, no progress — a gate that "mostly passed" failed.
4. **Output contract.** Every agent ends its final message with
   `## Summary / ## Why / ## Blocking / ## Non-blocking / ## Escalate to human`.
   `.claude/hooks/subagent_gate.py` parses it fail-closed: a missing contract is
   treated as Blocking; a non-empty `## Escalate to human` requires the parent to ask
   the human before proceeding.
5. **Instruction-quality gate.** Spawning an agent whose contract (or a guide it
   cites, or the core index files) is stale/ungraded/below threshold is blocked at
   SubagentStart by `.claude/hooks/instruction_gate.py`. The repair path is the
   `instruction-auditor` (itself exempt — gating the auditor would deadlock).
6. **Blind review before commit.** No commit ships unreviewed — see the managed
   governance block in `CLAUDE.md`.
7. **Escalation over improvisation.** Anything listed in
   `.agentic/guides/policy/escalation-policy.md` (human-gated commands, guarded write
   paths, `escalate_on` risk flags) stops the pipeline and goes to the human with
   concrete options.

## Reports

Inline reports: one section per finding, code refs as `file:line`. No executive
summaries, no conclusions, no emoji. Terseness is a feature — the human reads every
report.

## Context management (orchestrators)

Compact at ~80% context; `.claude/hooks/precompact_checkpoint.py` snapshots pipeline
state to `.claude/checkpoints/last-compaction.md` on PreCompact so a resumed session
can pick up mid-pipeline.
